article.headline: Utah Valley State 63, UMKC 61
article.story: OREM, Utah (AP) -- David Heck scored 18 points to lead Utah Valley State to a 63-61 victory Thursday night over Missouri-Kansas City. The Kangaroos (9-12) had a chance to win the game at the final buzzer, but Quinton Day's off-balance 25-footer from the left side of the court fell several feet short. With 5.2 seconds left and the Wolverines (12-11) leading 62-61, Richard Troyer had two free throws for Utah Valley. Troyer made the first and missed the second. Kalu Guasco grabbed the rebound for UMKC and passed to Day, who sprinted down the sideline before launching his final, failed shot. Pierre Thomas had 11 points for the Wolverines. Day led the Kangaroos with 14 points and five assists. Guasco added 13 points and five rebounds for Missouri-Kansas City. With 15 seconds left and Utah Valley State leading 62-59, Day had a clean look at a 3-pointer from the left wing that would have tied it. The shot rimmed out, but Guasco grabbed the rebound and laid it in to make the score 62-61 with 6.5 seconds remaining. The Kangaroos trailed 57-46 with five minutes to go, but Day and Guasco scored four points apiece down the stretch to help Missouri-Kansas City put together a 15-5 run. The Wolverines shot 4-for-9 from the free throw line over the final five minutes, including twice missing the front end of a one-and-one. Utah Valley State led 40-31 at halftime.
